President Trump met with Vice Premier Liu He of China to discuss trade negotiations and the possibility of a trade agreement. Both sides expressed optimism about the progress being made, but acknowledged that there are still some hurdles to overcome. The President mentioned that a meeting with President Xi Jinping could be scheduled in the near future. They also discussed the issue of fentanyl, with President Xi agreeing to criminalize its sale in China. The President expressed his appreciation for this commitment. Other topics of discussion included currency manipulation, technology transfers, and the possibility of lifting the ban on Huawei and ZTE. President Trump also commented on various domestic issues, such as the situation in Kashmir, the recent election fraud in North Carolina, and the Amazon deal in New York City.